public class ItemDepositorEntity extends PipeNetworkEntity
PipeNetworkEntity that can accept items from ItemExtractorEntitys moved "through" ItemPipeEntitys connected to the same PipeNetwork. The entity has a set of associated "filters" that the player chooses that designates which items can be transferred into it. If no filters are selected, all items can be transferred.

    • compare

      public int compare(PipeNetworkEntity other, net.minecraft.core.BlockPos pos)
      Used for sorting this entity in a list of other PipeNetworkEntitys relative to a sort block. Items with filters are always less than items without. This is so items are only transferred to ItemDepositorEntitys without filters only if there is no entity with a matching filter that can accept it. Otherwise, ItemDepositorEntitys are sorted from closet to farthest from the source block.
      Overrides:
      compare in class PipeNetworkEntity
      Parameters:
      other - The other PipeNetworkEntity to compare to.
      pos - The BlockPos to compare from
      Returns:
      -1 if the entity is less than the other PipeNetworkEntity, 1 if it is greater, otherwise 0 if they are equal.
